<L>__{interior courtroom day}
<A>__{richard kimble sits behind the desk, but already he's a shadow of the man we knew before, stares ahead passively as judge bennett delivers the sentencing to hushed courtroom.}
<C>__{judge bennett}
<D>__{after careful and studied review of all evidence presented during each phase of this proceeding, and because aggravated circumstances, detailed at length, were present the night of january 20th.}
<A>__{kimble is silent, stunned, but all around him the sentence shockwaves through the courtroom. reporters push out rear doors. prosecutors share a look with a hangman's satisfaction. nichols, watching behind kimble's table, lowers his head. disbelief.}
<B>__{angle on richard kimble}
<A>__{he remains silent. kimble is pulled gently to his feet by bailiff. gutherie whispers an "i'm sorry." kimble doesn't hear it.}
